{
     "text":"Barack Obama, the 44th President of the United States, was born in Honolulu, Hawaii on August 4, 1961. He served two terms from 2009 to 2017. His presidency was marked by the passing of the Affordable Care Act, commonly known as Obamacare. In 2009, he was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize for his efforts to strengthen international diplomacy. Michelle Obama, his wife, was the First Lady and is known for her work on childhood obesity and education. They currently reside in Washington, D.C., although they often visit their family home in Chicago. During his presidency, Obama worked closely with international organizations such as the United Nations and NATO. The Obama Foundation, based in Chicago, continues his legacy through community leadership programs worldwide.",
